\begin{remark}
This quantization model of nilpotent orbit closure is very different from the classical model given in \cite{Br 2003}. Namely, the Brylinski model is not necessarily of the form $U({\mathfrak{{g}}})/J(\lambda)$. In particular, when the classical nilpotent orbit closure $\overline{{\mathcal{{O}}}}$ is not normal (the classification of all such orbit closures is given in \cite{KP 1982}), the infinitesimal character of the Brylinski model $\lambda_{{\mathcal{{O}}}}$ always yields associated variety $AV(U({\mathfrak{{g}}})/J(\lambda_{{\mathcal{{O}}}})) = \overline{{\mathcal{{O}}}'}$, where ${\mathcal{{O}}}'$ is strictly smaller than ${\mathcal{{O}}}$.\\ 
